Package: libscanR
Type: Package
Title: Analysis and Visualization of Laser-Induced Breakdown Spectroscopy Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Raban", "Heller", email = "raban.heller@charite.de",
           role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8006-9742"))
Description: Provides a vendor-agnostic pipeline for importing, preprocessing,
    calibrating, and visualizing Laser-Induced Breakdown Spectroscopy (LIBS)
    spectral data. Supports baseline correction, peak identification against
    curated atomic emission line databases, univariate and multivariate
    calibration (including calibration-free LIBS and Saha-Boltzmann methods),
    elemental quantification with limit-of-detection and limit-of-quantification
    estimation, chemometric analysis (principal component analysis, partial
    least squares discriminant analysis, clustering) for tissue classification,
    and spatial elemental mapping. Includes an interactive 'shiny' application
    for spectral exploration. Designed for biomedical tissue analysis,
    environmental monitoring, and materials characterization workflows.
